From 125725345d88959ebf61e3d4408929f14579f05b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@tsm-consultz.local>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 22:14:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix critical shadow-duplication bug: O2C/CRM were serving
 abandoned strays

Root cause: app.use('/', express.static('html')) is registered before
app.use(express.static(__dirname)) in server.js. Every request to
/war-rooms/o2c/... or /war-rooms/crm/... was silently resolved against
html/war-rooms/{o2c,crm}/ -- single-commit, feature-incomplete, abandoned
duplicates -- rather than the real, actively-developed copies at repo-root
war-rooms/{o2c,crm}/.

Practical impact: everything built for O2C in the Cross-War Room Foundation
Modules session (control-plane fix, all 8 foundation modules, KPI cards
wiring) was never actually live. Production served a version with 1 of 4
control-plane scripts loaded and zero foundation module references.
Confirmed via node --check, script-tag balance, and a live local server
test hitting the real URL before/after.

Fix: migrated the real O2C and CRM (full history: initial build -> canonical-
core wiring -> foundation modules) into html/war-rooms/, overwriting the
abandoned strays. This also standardizes their location to match the
convention already used by CPQ, Catalog, MDM, Governance, Integration Hub,
and Digital Twin. Deleted repo-root war-rooms/ entirely -- nothing of value
left there.

Also preserved war-rooms/index.html (the Phase Command Center hub, driven
by architecture/kernel/phases.json + runtime/kernel/phase-loader.js) at
html/war-rooms/index.html, and fixed a pre-existing bug in it: its own
<script src="runtime/kernel/phase-loader.js"> was a relative path with no
leading slash, and no war-rooms/runtime/ directory has ever existed --
meaning PhaseLoader was never defined and the hub has never actually
worked, independent of the shadow bug. Now absolute: /runtime/kernel/phase-loader.js.

Also removed war-rooms/approval/services/approval-engine.js -- a 31-line
dead stub (2 hardcoded records, no SLA/KPI logic) that nothing referenced.
The real, working Approval engine is html/services/approval-engine.js
(165 lines, matches /api/approval/query's expected data shape) -- untouched,
was never shadowed since its URL path never collided with the stub's.

Verified locally: node --check clean on both migrated engines, script-tag
balance intact (16/16 O2C, 7/7 CRM), server boots and /war-rooms/o2c/...
now returns the foundation-wired version (8 references, up from 0),
/war-rooms/crm/... and /war-rooms/index.html both 200, phase-loader.js
now reachable at its absolute path.

phases.json NOT yet updated to register the 6 missing phases (Approval,
Catalog, MDM, Governance, Integration Hub, Digital Twin) -- separate
follow-up, its existing O2C/CRM entries already pointed at the correct
paths and needed no change since the html/ mount preserves URL compat.
